13.22	Tim_Severin	Tim Severin	Tim Severin (born 1940) is a British explorer, historian and writer. Severin is noted for his work in retracing the legendary journeys of historical figures. Severin was awarded both the Gold Medal of the Royal Geographical Society and the Livingstone Medal of the Royal Scottish Geographical Society. He received the Thomas Cook Travel Book Award for his 1982 book The Sinbad Voyage.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Tim_Severin.jpg/150px-Tim_Severin.jpg
